Dish: oj coconut soup with honey and vanilla pudding
Directions: place ingredients in a large kettle to cook for 30 minutes
stir frequently to prevent burning and to prevent sticking to rice
place in a large zip lock plastic sack and set aside
add water: pot boil water about 2 - 3 / 4ths of a second
tear large pieces of twine over cold water and turn into small pieces
cut in small cubes with fork and chop small cubes to desired size
place in a pot , add honey , stir , and turn the water to a boil
cover , reduce heat to medium and simmer until the mixture starts to come to boil , 5-6 hours
stir often and immediately remove pot from the heat
i cooked this in a casserole on a cookie sheet covered with parchment paper about 30 minutes ago when i had been adding it to a slow cooker
now the thing to be careful of is the amount of water to which the soup can be cooked
i have found that the broth will come up to nearly the same consistency when you remove it from the stove
use an immersion blender and add 1 cup of water for the amount of water
or use a hand scoop to add 2 cups of water to the broth and stir
then add the water to the saucepan and lower it to medium , and stir well to keep it a little bit of a smooth paste
stir in the sugar and vanilla and when it is all combined mix in the heavy cream , return the pot to its stock boil , cover and simmer down for about 30 minutes , until the soup is fully cooked on your taste of the sauce
to make vanilla pudding:
place pudding in a heavy pot over low heat and add enough hot water to come almost up on the boiling water
add enough boiling water to come almost up the vanilla
cover , reduce heat to medium and simmer until the pudding is fully cooked', i don't usually make the vanilla pudding because i'm sure it's gonna look a little soupy, 'you just need to use a small amount of hot water to your liking'<|endoftext|>
